How to create Own chart?


Phase 1: Create the Chart (Scaffolding)

Run the following command to generate the standard boilerplate.
Bash

helm create techessay-app

The Cleanup: By default, Helm adds a lot of "sample" code. For your GitHub repo, I recommend cleaning the templates/ folder and only keeping deployment.yaml, service.yaml, and _helpers.tpl to keep it concise for viewers.
Phase 2: Package the Chart

Before publishing, you must bundle the directory into a versioned, compressed archive (.tgz).

    Lint it: Check for syntax errors.
    Bash

helm lint ./techessay-app

Package it:
Bash

    helm package ./techessay-app

    Result: You now have a file named techessay-app-0.1.0.tgz.

Phase 3: Publish to a Repository

There are two main ways to do this in 2026: the Classic (GitHub Pages) way and the Modern (OCI) way.
Option A: Hosting on GitHub (Free & Great for Portfolios)

This uses your GitHub repository as a "Classic" Helm repo.

    Create a branch named gh-pages.

    Generate the Index: Helm needs an index.yaml to track available charts.
    Bash

helm repo index . --url https://<your-username>.github.io/<repo-name>/

Push: Upload the .tgz and the index.yaml to your gh-pages branch.

Usage: Users can now run:
Bash

    helm repo add techessay https://<your-username>.github.io/<repo-name>/

Option B: The Modern OCI Way (Using GitHub Packages)

This is the enterprise-standard approach. It treats the chart like a Docker image.

    Login to GitHub Container Registry (GHCR):
    Bash

echo $GITHUB_TOKEN | helm registry login ghcr.io -u <username> --password-stdin

Push the Chart:
Bash

helm push techessay-app-0.1.0.tgz oci://ghcr.io/<username>/charts

Usage: Users don't need repo add. They just pull directly:
Bash

    helm install my-app oci://ghcr.io/<username>/charts/techessay-app --version 0.1.0

Phase 4: Automation 

Since you’re building this for your GitHub, don't publish manually. Use GitHub Actions.
You can use the Chart Releaser Action to automate Phase 3:
YAML

# .github/workflows/release.yml
name: Release Charts
on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main
jobs:
  release:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Checkout
        uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Configure Git
        run: |
          git config user.name "$GITHUB_ACTOR"
          git config user.email "$GITHUB_ACTOR@users.noreply.github.com"
      - name: Run chart-releaser
        uses: helm/chart-releaser-action@v1.6.0
        env:
          CR_TOKEN: "${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}"
